 :tx/rationale "Create task: ZCM-2: Implement full INV-GUIDANCE-019 harvest urgency formula — four signals + hysteresis (INV-GUIDANCE-019, ADR-GUIDANCE-015). BACKGROUND: Currently harvest warning uses only tx_count/threshold. The spec defines four signals: (1) tx_since/dynamic_threshold (IMPLEMENTED), (2) minutes_since_harvest/30 (NOT IMPLEMENTED — time ceiling ensures harvest even during slow work), (3) high_value_unharvested/3 (NOT IMPLEMENTED — distinguishes knowledge-dense observations from routine task closures; counts datoms with :exploration/type that lack :harvest/promoted), (4) k_eff_critical (NOT IMPLEMENTED — Q(t) < 0.15 from INV-INTERFACE-007). Urgency = max of all four signals. Also implement ADR-GUIDANCE-015 hysteresis: once threshold increases, it stays high for at least 2 minutes (prevents oscillation during burst-then-pause patterns). APPROACH: (1) Add harvest_urgency_multi(store, k_eff) -> f64 to guidance.rs. (2) Implement each of the four signal computations. (3) Add hysteresis state (last_threshold_increase_time) to the computation. (4) Replace the single-signal check in should_warn_on_exit() with the multi-signal formula. (5) Update dynamic_threshold() to include hysteresis. ACCEPTANCE: (A) During a sprint (15 tx in 5 min, all task closures), urgency is LOW (signal 3 is 0 because no high-value datoms). (B) During knowledge capture (5 observations in 5 min), urgency is HIGH (signal 3 fires). (C) After 30 minutes without harvest, urgency fires regardless of tx count (signal 2). (D) At Q(t) < 0.15, urgency is critical regardless of other signals (signal 4). (E) Threshold increase persists for 2+ minutes (hysteresis). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs"
